WHO   — Lamont — the offered friendship
WHAT  — The hinge of the reform: proximity and friendship doing what no argument could — and, quietly, the protection that keeps Derek alive.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film's deepest claim is that hate is undone by contact, and Lamont is the contact.
HOW   — By being funny, decent, and unavoidable until the abstraction Derek hated became a person he couldn't.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  You don't have to like me, man. You just have to fold these sheets next to me every day — and that turned out to be enough.

